title: For Sale:  Wehrmacht K98 rifle by J.P. Sauer
postcontent: Wehrmacht K98 rifle by J.P. Sauer, 1943. Really nice combat used example with great patina and all matching parts. Usually Sauer bluing was very light on their K98s, though this one has held up very well. Receiver is Walther made, subcontracted for Sauer. Receiver is marked "CE", which is the code for J.P. Sauer. Rifle is numbered on nearly every part, as 1943 was the last year they really did full numbering of parts, which started to decline in 1944, the least parts being numbered on 1945 rifles. Stock is very nice, has original red stain seen on many Sauers of this era and has very nice Eagle/H (Heer) side cartouche and also waffenamts on bottom of butt. title: For Sale:  Wehrmacht K98 rifle by J.P. Sauer
postcontent: Wehrmacht K98 rifle by J.P. Sauer, 1943. Really nice combat used example with great patina and all matching parts. Usually Sauer bluing was very light on their K98s, though this one has held up very well. Receiver is Walther made, subcontracted for Sauer. Receiver is marked "CE", which is the code for J.P. Sauer. Rifle is numbered on nearly every part, as 1943 was the last year they really did full numbering of parts, which started to decline in 1944, the least parts being numbered on 1945 rifles. Stock is very nice, has original red stain seen on many Sauers of this era and has very nice Eagle/H (Heer) side cartouche and also waffenamts on bottom of butt. Though bluing is worn in some spots, as expected on a combat carried rifle, overall the rifle is near excellent. One blemish on the left side of the butt, but nothing big. I believe the sight hood may be a post war replacement, not sure.
